<br>
Sure you can.  I've rescued many from the lava in NToV.  Never had a problem CoHing FD monks, either.  Can't CoH people who have DA'd...they gotta click it off before the spell lands.<br>
<br>
Also, I think CoH also checks how far from the point of aggro.  Lemme run this by you.  On TZ, you got the 8-level PvP limit.  I was controlling a 60 mag (me!) and my lvl 47 druid in Chardok (both have faction).  I had killed several people at the zoneline...but they kept coming back.  I hate bind rushers, so I had to drive the point home.  Trained to zone-in with the druid and CoH'd back.  This worked a couple times except the time I aggro'd a mob in the castle (I was CoHing back to the first chamber behind castle, just before first bridge).  When the castle mob walked home, it ran back in after the druid and I had to gate him.<br>
<br>
Spell is weird.  It causes enough doubt sometimes to question its usefulness in some situations. <p><a href="http://home.elp.rr.com/scythek/everquest/">Tuis Kagato</a> - Arch Mage of Karana (<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=175764">Profile</a>) - <a href="http://www.pandemonium.cc/">Pandemonium!</a><br>

